CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1958, pg. A12 reads: "Gotham Beauties who helped make the Steel City sparkle during the 28th national conclave of Gay Northeasterners included two former Pittsbughers. Front: Janice King, Marion Wyatt and Alene Briggs-Brown, Thelma Spangler (former Pittsburghers) and Louise Moseley.  Back row: Lois Smallwood, Sally Parts, Edith Scott Johnson, one of the charter members of the Gays, and Grace Marshall."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nine Gay Northeasterner members, from left, front row: Janice King, Marion Wyatt, Alene Briggs-Brown, Thelma Spangler wearing halter dress, and Louise Moseley; back row: Lois Smallwood, Sally Parts, Edith Scott Johnson, and Grace Marshall, posed on steps in hallway of Penn Sheraton Hotel for grand ball
